==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loquacity
<hw>Lo*quac"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>loquacitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>loquacit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The habit or practice of talking continually or excessively;
inclination to talk too much; talkativeness; garrulity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Too great <qex>loquacity</qex> and too great taciturnity by
fits.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loquat</ent>⟦br⟧
